00:34:00,509 --> 00:34:01,870
To do this, we made some pretty cool tools,

680
00:34:01,910 --> 00:34:02,730
and here's just a couple.

681
00:34:03,090 --> 00:34:04,891
This is one of my favorites. It's called the Cave Tool.

682
00:34:04,911 --> 00:34:06,912
It was built by a multidisciplinary team,

683
00:34:07,393 --> 00:34:09,194
and it allowed us to be able to create Lego kits

684
00:34:09,294 --> 00:34:11,815
that had a logical system with a logical UI

685
00:34:12,075 --> 00:34:13,736
that could allow pretty much anyone on the team,

686
00:34:13,796 --> 00:34:15,097
and we tested it with producers,

687
00:34:15,137 --> 00:34:17,458
and producers could make caves that were fun.

688
00:34:17,918 --> 00:34:18,678
They had lighting.

689
00:34:19,159 --> 00:34:21,420
They had navigation, parkour, and collectibles,

690
00:34:21,860 --> 00:34:24,461
and this system allowed us to create the vast amount of caves

