main challenge was to use them all.

744
00:36:44,490 --> 00:36:45,812
So we've now built a beautiful world.

745
00:36:46,252 --> 00:36:47,914
It's got incredible gameplay.

746
00:36:47,954 --> 00:36:48,755
It's fun to play in.

747
00:36:49,376 --> 00:36:51,119
But it's not yet a living world, and our goal

748
00:36:51,159 --> 00:36:52,220
was to create a living world.

749
00:36:52,240 --> 00:36:54,783
So this is where we brought in Mikiel Lejaguar-Gigal.

750
00:36:54,803 --> 00:36:56,145
That's a bit of my Quebec co-author

751
00:36:56,165 --> 00:36:57,887
that I learned while I was up there.

752
00:36:58,008 --> 00:36:59,630
And he was the product owner for Living World.

753
00:37:01,152 --> 00:37:05,354
What Mike did is, surprise, surprise, he did his research and working with a historian,

754
00:37:05,374 --> 00:37:09,737
we made sure that he understood the people of ancient Greece, how the people lived, how they

755
00:37:09,797 --> 00:37:14,179
worked, where they slept, what tools they used, what did they wear, did they wear hats. Hats

756
00:37:14,219 --> 00:37:16,381
became incredibly important for some reason at some point.

757
00:37:18,182 --> 00:37:23,825
So he basically went in and did all of that research and then started working with his team to build the living world of Ancient Greece.

758
00:37:24,025 --> 00:37:31,769
So building on top of the meta AI system that was created for Assassin's Creed Origins, an incredibly powerful tool that meant that each NPC in the world has their own schedule.

759
00:37:32,109 --> 00:37:37,432
They need to go to work, they need to go to sleep, they need to go and pee, and they will have their life and they will do it.

760
00:37:37,812 --> 00:37:41,795
So you can follow them around and you can watch people as they move around the world living their life.

761
00:37:42,435 --> 00:37:49,120
One of the new things that we brought for Assassin's Creed Odyssey was the fact that they would actually not just do this live without paying attention to you, the player.

762
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:56,044
If you get caught by an NPC in Assassin's Creed Odyssey doing something that you shouldn't do, the thing that we introduced was the notion of smart objects.

763
00:37:56,405 --> 00:38:00,027
An NPC will react to the fact that you are doing something that you shouldn't be.

764
00:38:00,487 --> 00:38:03,432
If they're a courageous person, they will then go and find a nearby prop.

765
00:38:03,472 --> 00:38:06,496
It might be a spade, it might be a shovel, it might be a sword if they're lucky.

766
00:38:06,797 --> 00:38:09,801
And they'll bring that fight to you so that the loop of fighting continues.

767
00:38:10,141 --> 00:38:12,144
And some of them are pretty tough to beat as well.

768
00:38:13,526 --> 00:38:14,848
This also included the animal pass.

769
00:38:16,712 --> 00:38:20,275
We created over 450 individually motion captured stations

770
00:38:20,315 --> 00:38:21,696
for Assassin's Creed Odyssey,

771
00:38:21,796 --> 00:38:23,458
and we also built all of the props that we needed

772
00:38:23,478 --> 00:38:25,480
to make sure that they were using the correct items

773
00:38:25,520 --> 00:38:26,380
that they would do.

774
00:38:26,841 --> 00:38:29,403
But also using the system of Metair AI,

775
00:38:29,503 --> 00:38:31,525
it created thousands of different possibilities

776
00:38:31,705 --> 00:38:33,367
of living world scenarios that you could see

777
00:38:33,407 --> 00:38:34,568
taking place throughout the world.

778
00:38:35,678 --> 00:38:40,321
This also moved on to animals. We also wanted to bring mythology to the world

779
00:38:40,341 --> 00:38:43,363
and we haven't talked about it much but we drenched the world in different

780
00:38:43,383 --> 00:38:46,765
mythology and one of the ones we tapped into was the 12 labors of Hercules.

781
00:38:47,145 --> 00:38:50,767
So scattered throughout the world are these incredibly awesome legendary animals

782
00:38:51,167 --> 00:38:54,109
and these were part of the open living world that you could experience as you

783
00:38:54,129 --> 00:38:54,669
traveled around.

784
00:38:56,632 --> 00:38:58,634
So we're coming towards the end of production at this point

785
00:38:58,674 --> 00:38:59,875
and we move into phase five,

786
00:38:59,915 --> 00:39:01,596
which is what we call the final level pass.

787
00:39:01,616 --> 00:39:02,537
It's the quality pass.

